The ﬁrst factor gives solutions for θ of −4π/5, −2π/5, 0, 2π/5 and 4π/5. The second factor gives rise to solutions 0 and π, whilst the only value making the third factor zero is θ = 0. The solution θ = 0 appears in each of the above sets and so has multiplicity 3.

