5.25 By considering the diﬀerential
dG = d(U + P V − ST ),
where G is the Gibbs free energy, P the pressure, V the volume, S the entropy and T the temperature of a system, and given further that U, the internal energy, satisﬁes
dU = T dS − P dV ,
derive a Maxwell relation connecting (∂V /∂T )P and (∂S/∂P )T .

Given that dU = T dS − P dV , we have that

dG = d(U + P V − ST ) = dU + P dV + V dP − S dT − T dS = V dP − S dT .

